"title": "7482: Year of Jubilee",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7482",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Celebrated in the fiftieth year as the culmination of seven sabbatical years. During this year property was restored and Hebrew slaves were released. This year of liberation gave opportunity for a new start, and is alluded to as a type of the Messianic age.</p>\n<h2>The institution of the Year of Jubilee</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:8-Lev25:10\">LEV 25:8–25:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Land was left fallow in the Year of Jubilee</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:11-Lev25:12\">LEV 25:11–25:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:20-Lev25:22\">LEV 25:20–25:22</a> <em>These instructions apply to the sabbatical year. The Year of Jubilee may have been an additional fallow year, or may have coincided with the seventh sabbatical year.</em></p>\n<h2>The restoration of property in the Year of Jubilee</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:13\">LEV 25:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Regulating the value of property</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:15-Lev25:16\">LEV 25:15–25:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:16-Lev27:19\">LEV 27:16–27:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:23\">LEV 27:23</a></p>\n<h3>Underlining the fact that God is the true owner of the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:23-Lev25:24\">LEV 25:23–25:24</a></strong> <em>The restoration of property to those to whom God had originally entrusted it is a reminder that the land belongs to him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:43\">JOS 21:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:15\">1CH 29:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:13\">HEB 11:13</a></p>\n<h3>A means of preserving the inheritance from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:25-Lev25:28\">LEV 25:25–25:28</a></strong> <em>Families are urged to buy back land assigned to them by God. As a last resort, land is restored in the Year of Jubilee.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:32-Lev25:33\">LEV 25:32–25:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:24\">LEV 27:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:4\">NUM 36:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:7-Num36:9\">NUM 36:7–36:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:3\">1KI 21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:16-Ezek46:18\">EZK 46:16–46:18</a></p>\n<h2>The release of Hebrew slaves in the Year of Jubilee</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:15\">DEU 15:12–15:15</a></strong> <em>The release of slaves reflects God's redemption and preserves the freedom he has given</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:54-Lev25:55\">LEV 25:54–25:55</a></strong> <em>The Israelites may not be held permanently as slaves because they belong to God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:43\">LEV 25:39–25:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:50-Lev25:52\">LEV 25:50–25:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:8-Jer34:9\">JER 34:8–34:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:13-Jer34:14\">JER 34:13–34:14</a></p>\n<h2>The Year of Jubilee is the year of the Lord's favour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:18–4:19</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ alludes to the Year of Jubilee in proclaiming spiritual release and restoration.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a></p>",
